<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Notably in Timothy Tackett, "Interpreting the Terror" <i>French Historical Studies</i> <b>24</b>.4 (Autumn 2001:569-578); Tackett's view of swiftly evolving revolution in his <a href="/wiki/Prosopography" title="Prosopography">prosopography</a> of the deputies, <i>Becoming a Revolutionary: The Deputies of the French National Assembly and the Emergence of a Revolutionary Culture, 1789-1790</i> (Princeton University Press) 1996, was not fundamentally at variance with Schama.</li>
